FBIS4-62801 "drsov095_b_94020" FBIS-SOV-94-095 Daily Report 16 May 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Economic Issues Rise in Inflation Under 10 Percent in April Rise in Inflation Under 10 Percent in April LD1605100894 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 0400 GMT 16 May 94 LD1605100894 Moscow Russian Television Network Russian BFN [From the "Vesti" newscast] [Text] The rise in the rate of inflation was under 10 percent in April. According to a report on the state of the Russian economy prepared by experts from the Economics Ministry, in the first quarter of 1994 Russia's industrial output fell more sharply than ever. The number of loss-making enterprises more than doubled over the period and amounted to 18.6 per cent of all industrial enterprises by the end of March. Another trend recorded in the first quarter was more promising. According to the RosBusiness Consulting agency, release prices in Moscow fell for the first time in April. Inflation expectations also fell for the first time.
